{{Infobox South African town | name = Foreshore | native_name = | other_name = | image_skyline = Dias statue, Cape Town.jpg | image_caption = Statue of [[Bartolomeu Dias]] on the Heerengracht in the Foreshore | image_map = Cape Town Foreshore original coastline.svg | map_caption = Map showing the Foreshore and the approximate location of the original coastline | coordinates = {{coord|33.92|S|18.43|E|region:ZA|display=inline,title}} | province = Western Cape | district = | municipality = City of Cape Town | mainplace = Cape Town | established_date = | government_type = <!-- Ward 00 --> | leader_party = | leader_title = Councillor | leader_name = <!-- race --> | percent_black = 43.3% | percent_coloured = 11.2% | percent_asian = 6.3% | percent_white = 34.0% | percent_other = 5.2% <!-- language --> | demographics2_title1 = [[English language|English]] | demographics2_info1 = 78.3% | demographics2_title2 = [[Afrikaans]] | demographics2_info2 = 14.5% | demographics2_title3 = | demographics2_info3 = | demographics2_title4 = | demographics2_info4 = | demographics2_title5 = Other | demographics2_info5 = 7.2% | elevation_m = | postal_code = | area_code = | censuscode = 199041012 | website = | footnotes = }} The '''Foreshore''' is an area in [[Cape Town]], South Africa, situated between the historic city centre and the modern [[Port of Cape Town]]. It is built on land [[land reclamation|reclaimed]] from Table Bay in the 1930s and 1940s in connection with the construction of the Duncan Dock to replace the old harbour. Much of the Foreshore area is occupied by transport infrastructure for the port and [[Cape Town Railway Station]]. Other notable buildings in the area are the [[Cape Town Civic Centre]], the [[Artscape Theatre Centre]] and the [[Cape Town International Convention Centre]]. When the area was reclaimed, the Government undertook a detailed study (the Szlumper Commission) to decide how to utilize the land not needed by South African Railways. This resulted in the issuance of a detailed proposal, The Cape Town Foreshore Plan.<ref>See "The Cape Town Foreshore Plan: Final Report of the Cape Town Foreshore Technical Committee, 1947" (1948, Government Printer of the Union of South Africa).</ref>
