'''Kusunti''' (कुसुन्ती) is located in [[Lalitpur District, Nepal|Lalitpur]] sub-metropolitan city of [[Nepal]]. The area is small and is getting heavily populated in a short period of time. The reason behind this flow of people is the excavation of a large monument of [[Shiva|Lord Shiva]] with live snakes taking care of this holy area. It is believed that one of the local residents dreamt of the monument being under the earth. Moreover, she told the locals about the order of God to unearth the monument the very next day. This was found to be true and afterwards there occurred a flow of Hindus from all over the country to pay their homage to Lord Shiva. Now there is a beautiful [[temple]] sheltering the statue of Lord Shiva and is famous as Pancheswor Mahadev (पञ्चेश्वर महादेव) throughout the area and around the country.
