{{Use Australian English|date=May 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}} {{Infobox waterfall | name = Sherrard Falls | photo = | photo_width = 250px | photo_caption = | map = New South Wales | relief = yes | map_width = 250px | coordinates = {{coord|30|22|55|S|152|44|05|E|type:waterbody_region:AU-NSW_scale:50000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = <ref name=GNR>{{NSW GNR|id=TRqwjztLTR|title=Sherrard Falls|accessdate=15 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Gazetteer of Australia|id=NSW52865|name=Sherrard Falls (NSW)}}</ref> | location = [[New England (New South Wales)|New England]], [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]] | type = [[Waterfall#Types|Cascade]] | elevation = | height = | height_longest = | number_drops = | width = | average_width = | watercourse = ''unnamed stream'' | average_flow = | world_rank = }} The '''Sherrard Falls''' is a [[Waterfall#Types|cascade waterfall]] on an unnamed stream that is located in the [[New England (New South Wales)|New England]] region of [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]].
==Location and features== The waterfall is situated adjacent to the [[Waterfall Way]] between the town of {{NSWcity|Dorrigo}} and the locality of {{NSWcity|Thora}}, in the [[Dorrigo National Park]]. It is around {{convert|7|km}} from the town of Dorrigo and around {{convert|1|km}} from the [[Newell Falls]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.world-of-waterfalls.com/australia-sherrard-falls.html|title=Sherrard Falls|work=World of Waterfalls|date=|accessdate=15 May 2014}}</ref> The bridge across Sherrard Falls is one lane. Vehicular and pedestrian access and viewing of the Sherrard Falls is difficult due to no car parking on the narrow Waterfall Way.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.world-of-waterfalls.com/australia-newell-falls.html|title=Newell Falls and Sherrard Falls|work=World of Waterfalls|date=7 May 2008|accessdate=15 May 2014}}</ref> The Waterfall Way is subject to closure at Sherrard Falls and Newell Falls in times of high rain, due to flooding over the road.
