{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2015}}
The following is a timeline of the [[Santiago de Cuba#History|history]] of the city of [[Santiago de Cuba|Santiago]], [[Cuba]].
{{Dynamic list}}
{{TOC right}}

==Prior to 20th century==
{{History of Cuba}}

* 1514 - August: Santiago de Cuba founded.{{sfn|Bonavía|2003}}
* 1518 - [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Santiago de Cuba|Roman Catholic diocese of Baracoa]] established.<ref name=katolsk>{{cite web |title=Chronology of Catholic Dioceses: Cuba |url= http://www.katolsk.no/organisasjon/verden/chronology/cuba |publisher=[[Roman Catholic Diocese of Oslo]] |location=Norway |accessdate= January 7, 2016 }}</ref>
* 1522
** Capital of Cuba relocated to Santiago from [[Baracoa]].{{sfn|Catholic Encyclopedia|1908}}
** Coat of arms granted.{{sfn|Marley|2005}}
* 1526 - Fire.{{sfn|Marley|2005}}
* 1535 - Fire.{{sfn|Marley|2005}}
* 1603 - [[Raid on Santiago de Cuba (1603)|Sacked]] by English pirates.{{sfn|Marley|2005}}
* 1607 - Capital of Cuba relocated from Santiago to [[Havana]].{{sfn|Marley|2005}}
* 1613 - Fire.{{sfn|Marley|2005}}
* 1638 - [[Castillo de San Pedro de la Roca]] (fort) construction begins.
* 1722 - San Basilio el Magno seminary established.{{sfn|Marley|2005}}
* 1755 - Population: 15,471.{{sfn|Marley|2005}}
* 1767 - 11 June: Earthquake.{{sfn|Marley|2005}}
* 1774 - Population: 18,374.{{sfn|Marley|2005}}
* 1787 - [[Sociedad Económica de los Amigos del País]] founded.<ref>{{cite journal |title=Free Association and Civil Society in Cuba, 1787-1895 |author=Alfonso W. Quiroz |journal= [[Journal of Latin American Studies]] |volume=43 |number=1 |year= 2011 |doi=10.1017/S0022216X10001781 |subscription=yes }}</ref>
* 1805 - ''El Amigo de los Cubanos'' newspaper begins publication.{{sfn|Marley|2005}}
* 1808 - Population: 33,881.{{sfn|Marley|2005}}
* 1823 - Teatro Coliseo (theatre) opens.{{sfn|Bonavía|2003}}
* 1852 - Earthquake.{{sfn|Marley|2005}}
* 1862 - {{Interlanguage link multi|Tumba francesa La Caridad de Oriente|es|3=Tumba francesa La Caridad de Oriente|lt=Lafayette}} [[tumba francesa]] group founded.<ref name="Bodenheimer2015">{{cite book|author= Rebecca M. Bodenheimer |title= Geographies of Cubanidad: Place, Race, and Musical Performance in Contemporary Cuba|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=lRxlCgAAQBAJ|year=2015|publisher= [[University Press of Mississippi]] |location=USA |isbn=978-1-62674-684-8}}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media |url=https://archive.org/details/TumbaFrancesa |via=Internet Archive |year=2003 |title= Sociedad de Tumba Francesa La Caridad de Oriente, Santiago de Cuba |medium= Motion picture |publisher= Blackhole Factory |publication-place= Braunschweig, Germany }}</ref>
* 1868 - [[Santa Ifigenia Cemetery]] established.<ref name=EcuRed>{{cite web |title=[[EcuRed]] |publisher= {{Interlanguage link multi|Joven Club de Computación|es}} |location=Cuba |language=es |accessdate= }} Retrieved November 27, 2016</ref>
* 1898
** 3 July: [[Battle of Santiago de Cuba]] fought near city.{{sfn|Britannica|1910}}
** July: [[Siege of Santiago]] by US forces.
** ''El Cubano Libre'' newspaper in publication.[https://books.google.com/books?id=UBM-AQAAMAAJ&pg=PA160]
** [[Emilio Bacardí Moreau]] becomes mayor.{{sfn|Marley|2005}}
* 1899 - Public library established.<ref name=Valdes2005>{{citation |url=http://bvs.sld.cu/revistas/aci/vol14_1_06/aci10106.htm |language=es |title=Breve reseña sobre la biblioteca pública en Cuba antes de 1959 |author=Miguel Viciedo Valdés |work=[[Acimed]] |issn=1024-9435 |publisher=Centro Nacional de Informacion de Ciencias Medicas |location=Havana |year=2005 |volume=14 |number=1 }}</ref>

==20th century==

* 1902 - Population: 45,478.<ref>{{cite book |title=Statesman's Year-Book |year=1906 |location=London |publisher= Macmillan and Co.|chapter= Cuba |chapterurl= http://hdl.handle.net/2027/nyp.33433081590576?urlappend=%3Bseq=892 }}</ref>
* 1905 - Convención Bautista de Cuba Oriental (church) founded.<ref name="europa2004">{{cite book|title=Europa World Year Book |year=2004|publisher=[[Europa Publications]] |isbn=978-1-85743-254-1 |chapter=Cuba |chapterurl= https://books.google.com/books?id=wGA4o-UhAfgC&pg=PA1363 }}</ref>
* 1909 - Vista Alegre Theatre built.<ref name=cinema>{{cite web |url=http://cinematreasures.org/theaters/cuba/santiago-de-cuba?status=all |title=Movie Theaters in Santiago de Cuba, Cuba |work=CinemaTreasures.org |publisher= Cinema Treasures LLC |location=Los Angeles |accessdate= January 7, 2016 }}</ref>{{sfn|U.S. Merchant Marine|1920}}
* 1915 - Cine Aguilera (cinema) opens.<ref name=cinema />{{sfn|U.S. Merchant Marine|1920}}
* 1917 - Orientales baseball team formed.<ref name="Worth2013">{{cite book|author=Richard Worth|title=Baseball Team Names: a Worldwide Dictionary, 1869-2011|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oNVs03_8fEcC|year= 2013|publisher=[[McFarland & Company]] |location=USA |isbn=978-0-7864-9124-7}}</ref>
* 1919 - Population: 70,232.<ref>{{cite book |title=[[Statesman's Year-Book]] |year=1921 |location=London |publisher= Macmillan and Co.|chapter= Cuba |chapterurl= http://hdl.handle.net/2027/njp.32101072368440?urlappend=%3Bseq=837 |via=HathiTrust }}</ref>
* 1924 - Cine Rialto (cinema) opens.<ref name=cinema />
* 1943 - Population: 118,266.{{sfn|Marley|2005}}
* 1947 - [[University of Santiago de Cuba]] established.
* 1953
** 26 July: [[Moncada Barracks]] attacked by forces of Castro, launching the [[Cuban Revolution]].<ref name=europa2001chronology>{{cite book |title= Political Chronology of the Americas |year=2001|publisher=[[Europa Publications]] |isbn=978-1-85743-118-6 |chapter=Cuba |chapterurl= https://books.google.com/books?id=C7WayaUhkUEC&pg=PA79 }}</ref>
** Population: 163,237.{{sfn|Marley|2005}}
* 1954 - [[Antonio Maceo Airport]] opens.{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}}
* 1956 - 30 November: {{Interlanguage link multi|Levantamiento en Santiago de Cuba|es}} (anti-[[Fulgencio Batista|Batista]] event) occurs.
* 1957 - Anti-Batista unrest; crackdown.<ref>{{citation |work=New York Times |date= June 10, 1957 |title=Populace in revolt in Santiago de Cuba |url= https://www.nytimes.com/packages/html/books/matthews/matthews061057.pdf |author= [[Herbert Matthews]]}}</ref>
* 1964 - [[Estadio Guillermón Moncada]] (stadium) opens.
* 1970 - Population: 277,600.<ref>{{cite book |url= https://unstats.un.org/unsd/demographic/products/dyb/1970_round.htm |title=Demographic Yearbook 1975 |year=1976 |author=[[United Nations Department of Economic and Social Affairs]], Statistical Office |location=New York |chapter=Population of capital city and cities of 100,000 and more inhabitants |pages=253-279 }}</ref>
* 1976 - {{Interlanguage link multi|Jardín de los Helechos de Santiago de Cuba|es}} (garden) established.
* 1977 - [[Santiago de Cuba (baseball)|Avispas]] baseball team formed.<ref name="Worth2013" />
* 1999 - Population: 441,524.<ref name="europa2004" />

==21st century==

* 2012
** March: Catholic [[List of journeys of Pope Benedict XVI|pope visits]] Santiago.
** October: [[Hurricane Sandy]].<ref name=bbc-timeline>{{citation |work=BBC News |title=Cuba Profile: Timeline |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-19576144 |accessdate= January 7, 2016 }}</ref>
** Population: 431,471.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://unstats.un.org/unsd/demographic/products/dyb/dyb2013.htm |work=Demographic Yearbook 2013 |publisher=[[United Nations Statistics Division]] |title=Population of Capital Cities and Cities of 100,000 or More Inhabitants }}</ref>
* 2014 - Population: 434,268.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://unstats.un.org/unsd/demographic/products/dyb/dyb2014.htm |work=Demographic Yearbook 2014 |publisher= United Nations Statistics Division |title=Population of Capital Cities and Cities of 100,000 or More Inhabitants }}</ref>
* 2015 - September: Catholic [[List of pastoral visits of Pope Francis outside Italy|pope visits]] Santiago.

